node.text:
Each year, @f1 factories fall silent for 14 consecutive days, for what is known as the ‘Summer Shutdown’ 💤

Toto, James and Rob explain everything you need to know about the shutdown: from what it is, to why it takes place and what is and isn't allowed! 👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Mercedes-AMG PETRONAS F1 Team on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WHAT F1 SUMMER SHUTDOWN? APERIOD OF 14 CONSECUTIVE DAYS IN AUGUST, WHERE NO OPERATIONS RELATED το THE CAR ARE PERMITTED. OPERATION OF THE WIND TUNNEL AND CFD PRODUCTION AND DEVELOPMENT OF WIND TUNNEL, CAR, TEST AND TOOLING PARTS, SUB-ASSEMBLY OR ASSEMBLY OF CARS AND ANY WORK RELATED το THE DESIGN, DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCTION OF THE CAR IS NOT ALLOWED. POWER UNIT MANUFACTURERS MUST OBSERVE THESE SAME SHUTDOWN RULES.'.
